This paper deals with the problem of node classification in social networks, which is a common topic in the fields of social network analysis and machine learning. Therefore, cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.SOC (Social and Societal Computing) are the most likely categories. The paper also discusses various algorithms and techniques for node classification, which fall under the categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Finally, the paper mentions the use of information retrieval techniques for feature selection, which falls under the category of cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
